4df8afe2-d81f-48c2-bf02-61bf8c65c95b.title: Filliman Tarlock
4df8afe2-d81f-48c2-bf02-61bf8c65c95b.text:
Oh, I understand you! At last, someone who doesn't
just mumble. I understand what you're saying!

options.text: I'm wearing an amulet of ghost speak!
How long have you been a ghost?
What's it like being a ghost?

86fd5e59-7e46-4b5a-b467-496420068d45.title: <player>
86fd5e59-7e46-4b5a-b467-496420068d45.text: I'm wearing an amulet of ghost speak!

89e4ff5a-15c6-489a-b836-46d837d65b7f.title: Filliman Tarlock
89e4ff5a-15c6-489a-b836-46d837d65b7f.text:
Why you poor fellow, have you passed away and you
want to send a message back to a loved one?

fe043131-95b4-4abb-bf64-f1c35b9c3541.title: Filliman Tarlock
fe043131-95b4-4abb-bf64-f1c35b9c3541.text:
You have come to haunt my dreams until I pass on
your message to a dearly loved one. I understand.
Pray, tell me who would you like me to pass a message
on to?

56e10f7e-d710-4cad-9cfe-6ce565f1a17b.title: <player>
56e10f7e-d710-4cad-9cfe-6ce565f1a17b.text: Ermm, you don't understand... It's just that..

df8ed1b6-89cb-4ca5-b389-32a12abaa6e5.title: <player>
df8ed1b6-89cb-4ca5-b389-32a12abaa6e5.text:
Well, please don't be upset or anything... But you're
the ghost!

32fa964b-eb70-4c51-8fcc-21540faf85af.title: Filliman Tarlock
32fa964b-eb70-4c51-8fcc-21540faf85af.text: Don't be silly now! That in no way reflects the truth!

cb8d51c2-f3b9-4dc5-8b13-8eb55a4a5272.title: <player>
cb8d51c2-f3b9-4dc5-8b13-8eb55a4a5272.text: What's it like being a ghost?

0d8a6276-be5a-4a60-a358-2e221e9d4bd3.title: Filliman Tarlock
0d8a6276-be5a-4a60-a358-2e221e9d4bd3.text:
Oh, it's quite.... Oh... Trying to catch me out were you!
Anyone can clearly see that I am not a ghost!

317b8dde-0be1-40d8-85e8-a60ff32ae04a.title: <player>
317b8dde-0be1-40d8-85e8-a60ff32ae04a.text:
But you are a ghost, look at yourself! I can see
straight through you! You're as dead as this swamp!
Err... No offence or anything...

74d3902e-e7ba-4296-a178-c417fc614f40.title: Filliman Tarlock
74d3902e-e7ba-4296-a178-c417fc614f40.text:
No I won't take offence because I'm not dead and I'm
afraid you'll have to come up with some pretty
conclusive proof before I believe it. What a strange
dream this is.

ee2f86dd-d4d0-425c-8e5b-4aa822cbc7c6.title: Filliman Tarlock
ee2f86dd-d4d0-425c-8e5b-4aa822cbc7c6.text:
Oh, hello there, do you still think I'm dead? It's hard to
see how I could be dead when I'm still in the world. I
can see everything quite clearly. And nothing of what
you say reflects the truth.

3d0c27c0-c302-4d6b-ad55-61aba21ccb31.title: <player>
3d0c27c0-c302-4d6b-ad55-61aba21ccb31.text: Yes, I do think you're dead and I'll prove it somehow.

7b4c8170-32cb-4ff4-bdc0-20e5619b09fd.title: <player>
7b4c8170-32cb-4ff4-bdc0-20e5619b09fd.text: How long have you been a ghost?

52f47d0f-2f4b-4c5f-9cc9-1fa204c3bea8.title: Filliman Tarlock
52f47d0f-2f4b-4c5f-9cc9-1fa204c3bea8.text:
What?! Don't be preposterous! I'm not a ghost! How
could you say something like that?

b6422f72-ed71-41d9-bc56-d394c67f03c8.title: <player>
b6422f72-ed71-41d9-bc56-d394c67f03c8.text:
But it's true, you're a ghost... well, at least that is to
say, you're sort of not alive anymore.

b2b97cef-d7be-44ec-98e6-7a3af835a2d1.title: Filliman Tarlock
b2b97cef-d7be-44ec-98e6-7a3af835a2d1.text:
Don't be silly, I can see you, I can see that tree. If I
were dead, I wouldn't be able to see anything.. What
you say just doesn't reflect the truth. You'll have to try
harder to pull one over on me!

bff85758-ace4-4f35-b201-9288f879584b.title: <player>
bff85758-ace4-4f35-b201-9288f879584b.text:
Here take a look at this, perhaps you can see that
you're utterly transparent now!

327454e4-0fa1-4f70-bdfe-6eb9e11df33e.text:
The spirit of Filliman reaches forwards and takes the
mirror.

94e99246-d646-4a75-a7d0-15a001ac0352.title: Filliman Tarlock
94e99246-d646-4a75-a7d0-15a001ac0352.text:
Well, that is the most peculiar thing I've ever
experienced. This mirror must somehow be
dysfunctional. Strange how well it reflects the stagnant
swamp behind me, but there is nothing of my own

942f18b5-41d3-44e9-bf1a-00e4afdbd497.title: <player>
942f18b5-41d3-44e9-bf1a-00e4afdbd497.text:
That's because you're dead! Dead as a door nail..
Deader in fact... You bear a remarkable resemblance to
worm bait! Err.. No offence...

c78c5718-d0c8-4df7-b68c-a2298a05dd23.title: Filliman Tarlock
c78c5718-d0c8-4df7-b68c-a2298a05dd23.text:
I think you might be right my friend, though I still feel
very much alive. It is strange how I still come to be
here and yet I've not turned into a Ghast.

22fa9c16-8d58-48e5-91b4-f815060af954.title: Filliman Tarlock
22fa9c16-8d58-48e5-91b4-f815060af954.text:
It must be a sign... Yes a sign... I must try to find
out what it means. Now, where did I put my journal?

a5126237-ba65-4c4e-92ac-5e183001053a.title: Filliman Tarlock
a5126237-ba65-4c4e-92ac-5e183001053a.text:
Oh, hello... Sorry, you've caught me at a bad time, it's
just that I've had a sign you see and I need to find
my journal.

8f0feedc-c966-49b0-9bc6-dbf3e545432c.title: Filliman Tarlock
8f0feedc-c966-49b0-9bc6-dbf3e545432c.text:
Well, if I knew that, I wouldn't still be looking for it.
However, I do remember something about a knot?
Perhaps I was meant to tie a knot or something?

b6a92324-23f3-46b0-b881-71d7b0952b46.text: You give the journal to Filliman Tarlock.

9623c79d-e9d6-4ff1-b87d-8c7e6c8a7f89.title: <player>
9623c79d-e9d6-4ff1-b87d-8c7e6c8a7f89.text: Here, I found this, maybe you can use it?

d7d2c132-d98b-46a0-9a89-397cdc6f9dc8.title: Filliman Tarlock
d7d2c132-d98b-46a0-9a89-397cdc6f9dc8.text: My journal! That should help to collect my thoughts.

ed24cd1e-7438-4686-980d-46037cdcdd5a.text:
~ The spirit starts leafing through the journal. ~
~ He seems quite distant as he regards the pages. ~ 
~ After some time the druid faces you again. ~

15bd601c-567e-41c2-959a-cd4ac4981d59.title: Filliman Tarlock
15bd601c-567e-41c2-959a-cd4ac4981d59.text:
It's all coming back to me now. It looks like I came to
a violent and bitter end but that's not important now. I
just have to figure out what I am going to do now?

79d081a9-c009-4438-953f-aec0186b9859.title: Filliman Tarlock
79d081a9-c009-4438-953f-aec0186b9859.text:
Thanks for the journal, I've been reading it. It looks
like I came to a violent and bitter end but that's not
really important. I just have to figure out what I am
going to do now?

options.text: Being dead, what options do you think you have?

9147af86-c205-4e4e-a6e4-2cc93df101d7.title: <player>
9147af86-c205-4e4e-a6e4-2cc93df101d7.text:
Being dead, what options do you think you have? I'm
not trying to be rude or anything, but it's not like you
have many options is it? I mean, it's either up or down
for you isn't it?

503e786b-8261-42dd-a659-5f2a90227005.title: Filliman Tarlock
503e786b-8261-42dd-a659-5f2a90227005.text:
Hmm, well you're a poetic one aren't you. Your
material world logic stands you in good stead... If
you're standing in the material world...

ac646e5c-8ca6-42ac-bce1-ced2db8d3f27.title: Filliman Tarlock
ac646e5c-8ca6-42ac-bce1-ced2db8d3f27.text:
In my former incarnation I was Filliman Tarlock, a
great druid of some power. I spent many years in this
place, which was once a forest and I would wish to
protect it as a nature spirit.

e431d8dc-b48c-4db9-8f44-d3128b604d40.title: Filliman Tarlock
e431d8dc-b48c-4db9-8f44-d3128b604d40.text:
Will you help me to become a nature spirit? The
direction for becoming one are a bit vague. I need
three things but I know how to get one of them.
Perhaps you can help collect the rest?

ce7af038-9273-4e3a-9069-b339a688a969.title: <player>
ce7af038-9273-4e3a-9069-b339a688a969.text: I might be interested, what's involved?

0d217f4c-7ebe-4abb-a4c3-e53006fe2ea1.title: Filliman Tarlock
0d217f4c-7ebe-4abb-a4c3-e53006fe2ea1.text:
Well, the book stays that I need, and I quote:
'Something with faith', 'something from nature' and
'something of the 'spirit-to-become' freely given'. Hmm. I
know how to get something from nature.

3cb2573c-fb21-4b9d-b61a-bbab2dd08c07.title: <player>
3cb2573c-fb21-4b9d-b61a-bbab2dd08c07.text: Well, that does seem a bit vague.

53e7a810-0ebd-49fb-8ad8-b076cdeda713.title: Filliman Tarlock
53e7a810-0ebd-49fb-8ad8-b076cdeda713.text:
Hmm, it does and I could understand if you didn't
want to help. However, if you could perhaps at least get
the item from nature, that would be a start. Perhaps we
can figure out the rest as we go along.

f220eaea-73b1-4bcc-8866-9b70e4e86a9a.text:
The druid produces a small sheet of papyrus with some
writing on it.

04eb1cea-a024-4744-a373-26c5919884b4.title: Filliman Tarlock
04eb1cea-a024-4744-a373-26c5919884b4.text:
This spell needs to be cast in the swamp after you have
been blessed. I'm afraid you'll need to go to the temple
to the North and ask a member of the clergy to bless
you.

92af8be7-ed8c-435e-a9cf-77748ac479d6.title: Filliman Tarlock
92af8be7-ed8c-435e-a9cf-77748ac479d6.text:
It is required if you're to cast this druid spell. Once
you've cast the spell, you should find something from
nature. Bring it back to me and then we'll try to figure
out the other things we need.

fbc69a83-6e6e-4404-a605-c27641bed2e0.title: Filliman Tarlock
fbc69a83-6e6e-4404-a605-c27641bed2e0.text: Hello there, have you been blessed yet?

options.text: What are the things that are needed?
What should I do when I have those things?
I think I've solved the puzzle!
Could I have another bloom scroll please?

c18a07fb-fc93-48ab-8f9d-efa23af04488.title: <player>
c18a07fb-fc93-48ab-8f9d-efa23af04488.text: What are the things that are needed again?

b6665d89-151e-4e61-a733-5e9efc1eb977.title: Filliman Tarlock
b6665d89-151e-4e61-a733-5e9efc1eb977.text:
The three things are: 'Something with faith', 'something
from nature' and 'something of the spirit-to-become
freely given'.

3a46474e-50e6-44d1-9b07-68ab5d4e4d76.title: <player>
3a46474e-50e6-44d1-9b07-68ab5d4e4d76.text:
Ok, and 'something from nature' is the mushroom from
the bloom spell you gave me?

50b6a0f9-ab65-4c41-8f3f-66001aa35436.title: Filliman Tarlock
50b6a0f9-ab65-4c41-8f3f-66001aa35436.text:
Yes, that's correct, that seems right to me. The other
things we need are 'something with faith' and 'something
of the spirit-to-become freely given.

12829622-b475-432f-a5b9-f41e851b3d26.title: <player>
12829622-b475-432f-a5b9-f41e851b3d26.text: Do you have any ideas what those things are?

620b51bb-1bbe-4cbd-92be-9ddb597441ac.title: Filliman Tarlock
620b51bb-1bbe-4cbd-92be-9ddb597441ac.text: I'm sorry my friend, but I do not.

076acb49-1f65-446d-bc25-c4132bd8915e.title: Filliman Tarlock
076acb49-1f65-446d-bc25-c4132bd8915e.text: Did you manage to get something from nature?

8d06e52d-012a-4caa-8d63-f7101eda44cc.title: <player>
8d06e52d-012a-4caa-8d63-f7101eda44cc.text:
I picked a fungus that grew when I cast the bloom
spell.

eb4cf590-5c9f-4c47-84c4-1f5fec848f25.title: Filliman Tarlock
eb4cf590-5c9f-4c47-84c4-1f5fec848f25.text:
Wonderful, the mushroom represents 'something from
nature'. Now we need to work out what the other
components of the spell are!

8aff4c2f-31b1-4ac4-8f83-246112765500.title: <player>
8aff4c2f-31b1-4ac4-8f83-246112765500.text: What should we do when we have those things?

2495e27e-4e62-4890-b756-3052ac662d16.title: Filliman Tarlock
2495e27e-4e62-4890-b756-3052ac662d16.text:
Ah yes, I looked this up. It says,.. 'to arrange upon
three rocks around the spirit-to-become...'. Then I must
cast a spell. As you can see, I've already placed the
rocks. I must have planned to do this before I died!

ab6a26c5-ab6c-49a0-9331-72233b033830.title: <player>
ab6a26c5-ab6c-49a0-9331-72233b033830.text: Can we just place the components on any rock?

da6edba9-4c8d-46a0-bcd0-b062c0386403.title: Filliman Tarlock
da6edba9-4c8d-46a0-bcd0-b062c0386403.text:
Well, the only thing the journal says is that 'something
with faith stands south of the spirit-to-become', but I'm
so confused now I don't really know what that means.
Oh, if only I had all my faculties!

0cccc104-ebef-4055-b6ed-9b37ce2b191e.title: <player>
0cccc104-ebef-4055-b6ed-9b37ce2b191e.text: I think I've solved the puzzle!

f1cf4d4b-01f9-47ba-9f28-54ac7ade1ec6.title: Filliman Tarlock
f1cf4d4b-01f9-47ba-9f28-54ac7ade1ec6.text:
Oh really.. Have you placed all the items on the stones?
Ok, well, lets try! The druid attempts to cast a spell.

eed5c5db-2637-43d3-8754-a69b3f1f47d6.title: Filliman Tarlock
eed5c5db-2637-43d3-8754-a69b3f1f47d6.text:
Hmm, something still doesn't seem right. I think we
need something more before we can continue.

9efa09f9-5db1-4939-9ae6-ea16a91ba538.title: <player>
9efa09f9-5db1-4939-9ae6-ea16a91ba538.text: Could I have another bloom scroll please?

95bd2250-f081-4d47-8854-1e50c53d50ef.title: Filliman Tarlock
95bd2250-f081-4d47-8854-1e50c53d50ef.text: Sure, but please look after this one.

f4999604-dec3-405c-9343-fdcbc53565aa.text:
The spirit of Filliman Tarlock gives you another bloom
spell.

a3873e1c-911b-4280-90e8-c6d23148d1c9.title: Filliman Tarlock
a3873e1c-911b-4280-90e8-c6d23148d1c9.text:
Aha, everything seems to be in place! You can come
through now into the grotto for the final section of my
transformation.

c31d5556-dbce-4dba-9d4e-865c565ecd69.title: Filliman Tarlock
c31d5556-dbce-4dba-9d4e-865c565ecd69.text:
Hello again! I don't suppose you've found out what the
other components of the Nature spell are have you?

1373e1b5-635c-4582-b92a-26b4727f9eba.title: Filliman Tarlock
1373e1b5-635c-4582-b92a-26b4727f9eba.text:
Please come down into the grotto, we have much to
discuss.
